{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"47aa5223-d127-4cd1-8111-7ccc8f670170","content":"Found **1 untestable static** in your project:\n\n| File | Line | Call | Issue |\n|------|------|------|-------|\n| `views.py` | 3 | `datetime.now()` | Hard-coded time source; can't control in tests |\n\n**Why it's a problem:** Tests that depend on `datetime.now()` are non-deterministic — they can't assert exact values and may flake around midnight/DST boundaries.\n\n**Recommended fix for Django:** Replace with `django.utils.timezone.now()` and mock it in tests using [`freezegun`](https://github.com/spulec/freezegun) or `unittest.mock.patch`:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThen in tests:\n```python\nfrom freezegun import freeze_time\n\n@freeze_time(\"2026-01-15 12:00:00\")\ndef test_index(self):\n    ...\n```\n\nThis is a small project with only one call site, so the fix is straightforward. Want me to apply it?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8e4b4eda-20e4-4e01-8896-de11cd14cdde","outputTokens":280,"requestId":"702D:1A47AE:42C758:4E43C7:69F2C165"},"id":"128d024d-8228-4b4e-9a81-6a67233d00ad","timestamp":"2026-04-30T02:41:49.632Z","parentId":"e880decd-2577-444c-8458-3c9ae81a4939"}
